Q5.   Write a python program to delete the age properties of the user.
Ans.   class user:
            name=input("Enter Your Name: ")
            age=int(input("Enter Your Age: "))
            print(name,age)
            del age
            print(name)
       u1=user()
       
Q6.   Write a python program to create 3 user objects and find the Youngest to all.
Ans.   class user:
            def __init__(self):
                  self.m1=int(input("Enter 1st Student Marks: "))
                  self.m2=int(input("Enter 2nd Student Marks: "))
                  self.m3=int(input("Enter 3rd Student Marks: "))
            def show(self):
                  if self.m1>self.m2 and self.m3:
                       print("S1")
                  elif self.m2>self.m1 and self.m3:
                       print("S2")
                  else:
                       print("S3")
         u1=user()
         u1.show()
         
Q7.   Write a python program to create a Laptop class with 4 attributes(brand,ram,cpu,hdd) and 2 methods(showconfig() to print the value,
           __init__()to initillize the values.) 
Ans.   class Laptop:
            def __init__(self):
                self.brand=input("Enter Your Device Brand: ")
                self.ram=int(input("Enter Your Device RAM: "))
                self.cpu=eval(input("Enter Your Device CPU: "))
                self.hdd=eval(input("Enter Your Device HDD: "))
             def showconfig(self):
                print("Brand:- ",self.brand,"RAM:- ",self.ram,"CPU:- ",self.cpu,"HDD:- ",self.hdd,end="\n")
        L1=Laptop()
        l2=Laptop()
        l1.showconfig()
        l2.showconfig()
        
Q8.   Write 7th Question,Create 3 Laptop object and add them to the list in the sorted order based on the RAM size.
Ans.    class Laptop:
           def __init__(self):
                self.brand=input("Enter Your Device Brand: ")
                self.ram=int(input("Enter Your Device RAM: "))
                self.cpu=eval(input("Enter Your Device CPU: "))
                self.hdd=eval(input("Enter Your Device HDD: "))
           def show(self):
                print(self.brand,self.ram,self.cpu,self.hdd,end="\n")
                sorted(self.ram)
                L1=[]
                L1.append(self.ram)
                print(L1)
        P1=Laptop()
        P2=Laptop()
        P3=Laptop()
        P1.show()
        p2.Show()
        P3.show()
        
Q9.   Write a python program to create a school class and 3 instance variable and 1 class variable.
Ans.   class School:
             course=input("Enter Course: ")    #Class Variable
             def __init__(self):
                    self.name=input("Enter Your Name: ")
                    self.id=input("Enter Your Id: ")
              def show(self):
                    print("Name:- ",self.name,"ID:- ",self.id,end="\n")
         s1=School()
         s2=School()
         s1.show()
         s2.show()
         print(s1.course)
         print(s2.course)
         
         
Q10.  Define a class Employee with instance object variable empid,name,salary.Write __Init__()method in the class to initilize instance object variable.
          Also Define instance method to input field and dispaly field values.
Ans.   class Employee:
              def __init__(self):
                   self.empid=input("Enter Your Emp. Id: ")
                   self.name=input("Enter Your Name: ")
                   self.salary=eval(input("Enter Your Salary: "))
               def showdata(self):
                   print("Id:- ",self.empid,"Name:- ",self.name,"Salary:- ",self.salary,end="\n")
       E1=Employee()
       E2=Employee()
       E1.showdata()
       E2.showdata()
        
        
